<plot>In 1943, future renowned feature film still photographer Louis Goldman is 17 when he and his family have crisscrossed Europe and trekked over the treacherous Alps, barely ahead of the Nazis. Italian peasants have helped Louis's father undergo emergency surgery, in time for the Goldmans' journey to their last hope - a secret rescue operation in Florence. There, the cardinal and his diocesan priests risk their lives to save Louis Goldman, his mother, father, and 12-year-old brother, Harry - among many other Jews who are hunted by the Germans and Italian Fascists.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?204507</url></doc>
